MedComCore

The official URL for this implementation guide is: 

http://medcomfhir.dk/fhir/core/1.0/ImplementationGuide/dk.fhir.ig.medcom-core

The DK MedCom Core IG

resource.name: MedComCoreEncounter
resource.description: An interaction between a patient/citizen and healthcare provider(s) for the purpose of providing healthcare service(s) or assessing the health status of a patient/citizen.

resource.description: Encounter which is part of an episode of care reported to the Danish National Patient Registry

resource.name: MedComCorePatient
resource.description: Patient/citizen resource to use as subject in MedCom communication

resource.name: MedComHospitalNotificationEncounter
resource.description: Encounter derivation that handles hospital notification when a patient is admitted to a hospital. The hospital notification is always send from a hospital. The receiver of the message is the patients home municipalicy. The hospital notification is send for example when patient is admitted, on leave, returned from leave, finished hospital stay.

resource.name: MedComHospitalNotificationMessage
resource.description: A message for a Hospital Notification. The message is triggered as patients are admitted, onleave or has finished a hospital stay in order to notify the relevant Municipalicy home care

resource.name: MedComHospitalNotificationMessageHeader
resource.description: Message header for a hospital notification message.
